<subSubSection id="F2BBA1DDB8AD2F4847B89D7BB3CBA6DE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="EBBFC1A89ECBE05705D63467A3AC7D84" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="048E4EFDFCB36241AB2F25E7CCD34AD0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Variable twining perennial or liana to 6 m, stems (and leaves) glabrous to tomentellous. Leaves petiolate, 4-12 
<normalizedToken id="E1BFE8A9508F7C454B40CFF5FD804863" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4-12 cm, ovate, shortly acuminate, cordate, with rounded auricles, adaxially glabrous, abaxially glabrous, pubescent or tomentellous; petioles 2.5-5.5 cm. Inflorescence typically many-flowered, subcorymbose in form or a raceme of umbels; peduncles 2-9(-20) cm; bracteoles caducous, scale-like; secondary peduncles 3-5 cm; tertiary peduncles 1-1.5 cm; pedicels 5-20 mm; sepals unequal, outer 7-8 
<normalizedToken id="EC572C901F46ABD86EC4566422326176" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-4 mm, ovate, obtuse, scarious-margined, glabrous, inner 8-10 
<normalizedToken id="3AF1D92907606BBF83D1BD55E509B9FA" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4-5 mm, oblong-elliptic, rounded to retuse, margins broad, scarious; corolla (3-)3.5-4.5 cm long, white, funnel-shaped, glabrous, limb 2.5 cm diam. Capsules 9-10 
<normalizedToken id="CAF28850EAE23AC3C60EB67E2C31E96D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
8-12 mm, subglobose, glabrous; seeds 6 
<normalizedToken id="3169F1DC5E99A162200B8ED630F73C59" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3 mm, pilose with long cilia c. 8 mm in length.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
